snippet.title: Amber Heard Was Hit By Johnny Depps Iphone In Domestic Fight
snippet.description: Amber Heard the actress who starred in "The Danish Girl" accused her husband, Johnny Depp of physically assaulting her during a heated argument. Heard appeared in court today to ask for a temporary restraining order against Depp and she detailed a history of physical abuse suffered at the hands of her husband. Heard and her attorney Samantha Spector actually brought photographs of her bruised face which heard alleged was from Depp hitting her with an iphone last saturday night. Then she filed a divorce the following weekend. The fight took place one day after Depp's mother, Betty Sue Palmer died after battling an undisclosed illness.

snippet.description: Johnny Depp repeatedly tells Amber Heard to "cut" him as she begs him not to hurt himself in disturbing audio played to the High Court yesterday. ¬†The 57-year-old actor is suing The Sun‚Äôs publisher News Group Newspapers and the paper‚Äôs editor, Dan Wootton, over an article published in 2018 that referred to him as a ‚Äúwife beater‚Äù. ¬†In the muffled audio, Depp says: ‚ÄúYou wanna cut me. Cut me wherever you want. ¬†‚ÄúYou wanna cut me somewhere. On the arm, chest? Where do you wanna start? Cut me." ¬†Heard says: "Don't cut your skin. ¬†‚ÄúPlease do not cut your skin.   ¬†‚ÄúWhy would you do that? Please do not." ¬†Depp then says: ‚ÄúIt's easy.‚Äù ¬†Heard says: ‚ÄúPlease do not do that. Please do not cut yourself. You don't need to cut yourself.‚Äù ¬†Depp tells Heard that ‚ÄúI want your mark‚Äù and then says: ‚ÄúCut cut, cut.‚Äù ¬†He then calls her a ‚Äúp***y‚Äù and tells her: ‚ÄúYou f***ing hate me, come on.‚Äù   ¬†The court was told the recording came in July 2016 when their tumultuous relationship was coming to an end. ¬†In May 2016, Heard filed for divorce citing irreconcilable differences. ¬†Asking Depp about the audio, Sasha Wass QC said: "You're threatening to cut yourself in front of Ms Heard and you're actually holding a knife at the time."  ¬†Depp replied: "I was asking her to cut me.  ¬†‚ÄúIf she wasn‚Äôt willing I would do it myself." ¬† The court has previously heard that Depp called Heard a "gold-digging c*m guzzler" in explosive text messages sent to a friend.   ¬† In another revelation, it emerged that the Pirates of the Caribbean star made "Amber Turd" jokes after blaming her for poo he found in their bed the day after her 30th birthday party on April 21, 2016. ¬†Depp denies ever hitting his ex-partner Heard and rejects her claims that he was violent during their brief 18-month marriage.

snippet.title: Vanessa Paradis Breaks Her Silence On Johnny Depp Allegedly Assaulting Amber Heard
snippet.description:
Vanessa Paradis, Johnny Depp‚Äôs ex and the mother of his children, is breaking her silence for the first time after Amber Heard claimed that Johnny physically assaulted her. In a handwritten letter, Vanessa defends her ex and calls Amber‚Äôs claims ‚Äòoutrageous.‚Äô
Vanessa Paradis, 43, is finally speaking out following Amber Heard‚Äôs shocking claims that Johnny Depp allegedly hit her multiple times throughout their short marriage. Vanessa, who has two children with the Pirates of the Caribbean actor, had a jaw-dropping reaction to the allegations against her longtime partner! Click through to read Vanessa‚Äôs letter defending Johnny!
Vanessa penned a letter, obtained by TMZ, in defense of her former partner of 14 years on May 27, saying that he had never been physically abusive with her in the entire time she had ever known him. Her shocking letter comes just days after Amber‚Äôs allegations of domestic abuse went public, and Vanessa, who was with Johnny from 1998-2012, and had daughter Lily-Rose, 17, and Jack, 14, wanted to call her bluff:

‚ÄúJohnny Depp is the father of my two children, he is a sensitive, loving and loved person, and I believe with all my heart that these recent allegations being made are outrageous, in all the years I have known Johnny, he has never been physically abusive with me, and this looks nothing like the man I lived with for 14 wonderful years.‚Äù She signed it Vanessa Paradis

Amber filed a restraining order against Johnny on May 27. She also revealed shocking photos of her bruised face. Amber claimed that one of the photos was taken after Johnny allegedly hit her on May 21, according to TMZ. She also accused him of smashing her iPhone into her face and that he paid her to keep quiet about the alleged abuse.
